UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393204001199
KW  - Price stability
KW  - Tax distortions
KW  - Optimal monetary policy
AB  - We investigate the case for price stability in the general version of the New Keynesian (NNS) model with capital and several shocks. The model includes, in addition to the standard imperfect competition and monetary frictions, a non-trivial, endogenous tax distortion. We find that the case for perfect price stability is not significantly weakened. Optimal policy tolerates a small amount of output gap and price variability by reacting less strongly to supply and fiscal shocks in comparison to a policy that aims at perfect price stabilization.
